33-- ----------------------  Content type
34
35-- | Character sequence.
36type Chars = String
37
38-- | Mapping from chars to chars.
39type CharsMap = O.Map Chars

41{-# WARNING ContentEmpty   "Use 'empty' instead." #-}
42{-# WARNING ContentBool    "Use 'pBool' instead." #-}
43{-# WARNING ContentDec     "Use 'pDec' instead." #-}
44{-# WARNING ContentClock   "Use 'pClock' instead." #-}
45{-# WARNING ContentTime    "Use 'pTime' instead." #-}
46{-# WARNING ContentCode    "Use 'pCode' instead." #-}
47{-# WARNING ContentTerm    "Use 'pTerm' instead." #-}
48{-# WARNING ContentText    "Use 'pText' instead." #-}
49{-# WARNING ContentList    "Use 'pList' instead." #-}
50{-# WARNING ContentSet     "Use 'pSet' instead." #-}
51{-# WARNING ContentTie     "Use 'pTie' instead." #-}
52{-# WARNING ContentRel     "Use 'pRel' instead." #-}
53{-# WARNING ContentInterp  "Use 'pInterp' instead." #-}
54{-# WARNING ContentType    "Use 'pType' instead." #-}
55{-# WARNING ContentEnd     "Use 'end' instead." #-}

57-- | The Baala content type.
58data Content
59    = ContentEmpty              -- ^ __1.  Edge:__                   Sign of no ordinary type
60    | ContentBool   Bool        -- ^ __2.  Numeric:__                Boolean type
61    | ContentDec    T.Decimal   -- ^ __3.  Numeric:__                Decimal number type
62    | ContentClock  T.Clock     -- ^ __4.  Numeric:__                Clock type
63    | ContentTime   T.Time      -- ^ __5.  Numeric:__                Time type
64    | ContentCode   Chars       -- ^ __6.  Textual:__                Code type
65    | ContentTerm   S.TermName  -- ^ __7.  Textual:__                Term name type
66    | ContentText   Chars       -- ^ __8.  Textual:__                Text type
67    | ContentList   [Content]   -- ^ __9.  Recursive, Collective:__  List type
68    | ContentSet    [Content]   -- ^ __10. Recursive, Collective:__  Set type
69    | ContentTie    [TermC]     -- ^ __11. Recursive, Relational:__  Tie type (set of terms)
70    | ContentRel    RelC        -- ^ __12. Recursive, Relational:__  Relation type
71    | ContentInterp T.Interp    -- ^ __13. Meta, Relational:__       Interpretation type
72    | ContentType   T.Type      -- ^ __14. Meta:__                   Type for type
73    | ContentEnd                -- ^ __15. Edge:__                   The end of everything
74    deriving (Show)
75
76instance Eq Content where
77    x == y  = compare x y == EQ
78    x /= y  = compare x y /= EQ
79
80instance Ord Content where
81    -- simple
82    compare (ContentBool    x) (ContentBool    y)  = compare x y
83    compare (ContentDec     x) (ContentDec     y)  = compare x y
84    compare (ContentClock   x) (ContentClock   y)  = compare x y
85    compare (ContentTime    x) (ContentTime    y)  = compare x y
86    compare (ContentCode    x) (ContentCode    y)  = compare x y
87    compare (ContentTerm    x) (ContentTerm    y)  = compare x y
88    compare (ContentText    x) (ContentText    y)  = compare x y
89
90    -- complex
91    compare (ContentList    x) (ContentList    y)  = compare x y
92    compare (ContentSet     x) (ContentSet     y)  = compareAsSet x y
93    compare (ContentTie     x) (ContentTie     y)  = compareAsSet x y
94    compare (ContentRel     x) (ContentRel     y)  = compare x y
95    compare (ContentInterp  x) (ContentInterp  y)  = compare x y
96    compare (ContentType    x) (ContentType    y)  = compare x y
97
98    -- others
99    compare x y  = D.typeOrder x `compare` D.typeOrder y
100
101-- | Compare two lists as two sets.
102compareAsSet :: (Ord a) => [a] -> [a] -> Ordering
103compareAsSet x y = compare (Set.fromList x) (Set.fromList y)
104
105-- | Empty content.
106instance B.Default Content where
107    def = D.empty
108
109instance D.Basis Content where
110    typeOf (ContentEmpty    )  = T.TypeEmpty
111    typeOf (ContentBool    _)  = T.TypeBool
112    typeOf (ContentDec     _)  = T.TypeDec
113    typeOf (ContentClock   c)  = T.TypeClock $ Just $ T.clockPrecision c
114    typeOf (ContentTime    t)  = T.TypeTime  $ Just $ T.timePrecision t
115    typeOf (ContentCode    _)  = T.TypeCode
116    typeOf (ContentTerm    _)  = T.TypeTerm
117    typeOf (ContentText    _)  = T.TypeText
118    typeOf (ContentList   cs)  = T.TypeList $ typeSum cs
119    typeOf (ContentSet    cs)  = T.TypeSet  $ typeSum cs
120    typeOf (ContentTie    cs)  = T.TypeTie  (D.typeOf O.<$$> cs)
121    typeOf (ContentRel     _)  = T.TypeRel []
122    typeOf (ContentInterp  _)  = T.TypeInterp
123    typeOf (ContentType    _)  = T.TypeType
124    typeOf (ContentEnd      )  = T.TypeEnd
125
126typeSum :: D.Basis c => [c] -> T.Type
127typeSum cs = case B.unique $ map D.typeOf cs of
128               [t] -> t
129               ts  -> T.TypeSum ts
130
131instance D.CContent Content where
132
133instance B.MixEncode Content where
134    mixTransEncode sh c =
135        case c of
136          ContentCode  s   -> B.mixString $ quote  (sh s) s
137          ContentText  s   -> B.mixString $ qquote (sh s) s
138          ContentTerm  s   -> B.mixString $ "'" ++ S.termNameString s
139          ContentDec   n   -> B.mixString $ T.encodeDecimal n
140          ContentClock t   -> B.mixEncode t
141          ContentTime  t   -> B.mixEncode t
142          ContentBool  b   -> B.mixEncode b
143          ContentEmpty     -> B.mixString "()"
144          ContentEnd       -> B.mixString "(/)"
145
146          ContentList cs   -> D.mixBracketList $ mixBar cs
147          ContentSet  cs   -> D.mixBracketSet  $ mixBar cs
148          ContentTie  ts   -> S.bracketWith S.bracketTie $ T.termsToMix1 sh ts
149          ContentRel  r    -> B.mixTransEncode sh r
150          ContentInterp i  -> B.mixEncode i
151          ContentType t    -> S.bracketWith S.bracketType $ B.mixEncode t
152        where
153          mixBar cs   = B.mixJoinBar $ map (B.mixTransEncode sh) cs
154
155quote :: Maybe Chars -> CharsMap
156quote (Nothing) t   = "'" O.++ t
157quote (Just t)  _   = t
158
159qquote :: Maybe Chars -> CharsMap
160qquote (Nothing) t | O.tIsEmpty t  = "\"\""
161                   | otherwise     = S.angleQuote t
162qquote (Just t)  _                 = t
163

165-- ----------------------  Edge
166
167instance D.CEmpty Content where
168    empty                       = ContentEmpty
169    isEmpty ContentEmpty        = True
170    isEmpty _                   = False
171
172instance D.CEnd Content where
173    end                         = ContentEnd
174    isEnd ContentEnd            = True
175    isEnd _                     = False
176

184    isBool _                    = False

272-- ----------------------  Dispatch
273
274-- | Constants for edge content, i.e., empty and end.
275type DispatchEdge a = ( a, a )
276
277-- | Functions for simple content, i.e.,
278--   boolean, decimal, clock, time, code, term, and text.
279type DispatchSimple a =
280    ( Bool        -> a
281    , T.Decimal   -> a
282    , T.Clock     -> a
283    , T.Time      -> a
284    , Chars       -> a
285    , S.TermName  -> a
286    , Chars       -> a
287    )
288
289-- | Functions for complex content, i.e.,
290--   list, set, tie, relation, interp, and type.
291type DispatchComplex a =
292    ( [Content]   -> a
293    , [Content]   -> a
294    , [TermC]     -> a
295    , RelC        -> a
296    , T.Interp    -> a
297    , T.Type      -> a
298    )
299
300-- | Call type-specific functions on empty or end content.
301dispatchEdge :: DispatchEdge a -> (Content -> a) -> (Content -> a)
302dispatchEdge (empty, end) other c =
303    case c of
304      ContentEmpty    -> empty
305      ContentEnd      -> end
306      _               -> other c
307
308-- | Call type-specific functions on simple content.
309dispatchSimple :: DispatchSimple a -> (Content -> a) -> (Content -> a)
310dispatchSimple (bool, dec, clock, time, code, term, text) other c =
311    case c of
312      ContentBool   b -> bool  b
313      ContentDec    n -> dec   n
314      ContentClock  t -> clock t
315      ContentTime   t -> time  t
316      ContentCode   s -> code  s
317      ContentTerm   s -> term  s
318      ContentText   s -> text  s
319      _               -> other c
320
321-- | Call type-specific functions on complex content.
322dispatchComplex :: DispatchComplex a -> (Content -> a) -> (Content -> a)
323dispatchComplex (list, set, tie, rel, interp, type_) other c =
324    case c of
325      ContentList   cs -> list   cs
326      ContentSet    cs -> set    cs
327      ContentTie    ts -> tie    ts
328      ContentRel     r -> rel    r
329      ContentInterp  i -> interp i
330      ContentType    t -> type_  t
331      _                -> other  c
332
333-- | Call type-specific functions on content.
334dispatchContent :: DispatchEdge a -> DispatchSimple a -> DispatchComplex a -> (Content -> a)
335dispatchContent e s c = simple where
336    simple  = dispatchSimple s edge
337    edge    = dispatchEdge e complex
338    complex = dispatchComplex c other
339    other   = B.bug "dispatchContent"
340
341
342-- ----------------------  Concrete type
343
344-- | @Judge@ for concrete baala content.
345type JudgeC = T.Judge Content
346
347-- | @Term@ for concrete baala content.
348type TermC = S.Term Content
349
350-- | @Rel@ for concrete baala content.
351type RelC = T.Rel Content
352
353-- | Abortable content.
354type AbC = B.Ab Content
355
356-- | Concrete dataset.
357type DatasetC = D.Dataset Content
358
359-- | Shorthand function for the Baala content type.
360--
361--   >>> the $ D.pText "a"
362--   ContentText "a"
363--
364the :: Content -> Content
365{-# INLINE the #-}
366the = id
367
368-- | Decode the Baala content from string.
369--
370--   Edge contents.
371--
372--     >>> stringC "()"
373--     Right ContentEmpty
374--
375--     >>> stringC "(/)"
376--     Right ContentEnd
377--
378--   Numeric contents.
379--
380--     >>> stringC "(+)"
381--     Right (ContentBool True)
382--
383--     >>> stringC "12.00"
384--     Right (ContentDec Decimal (2) 12)
385--
386--     >>> stringC "|02:30:00|"
387--     Right (ContentClock |02:30:00|)
388--
389--     >>> stringC "2013-04-18"
390--     Right (ContentTime 2013-04-18)
391--
392--   Textual contents.
393--
394--     >>> stringC "'foo"
395--     Right (ContentCode "foo")
396--
397--     >>> stringC "'/foo"
398--     Right (ContentTerm "foo")
399--
400--     >>> stringC "\"foo\""
401--     Right (ContentText "foo")
402--
403--   Metadata contents.
404--
405--     >>> stringC "{| Aaa /x bbb /y ccc. |}"
406--     Right (ContentInterp (Interp { interpWords = ..., interpTerms = ... }))
407--
408--     >>> stringC "[- text -]"
409--     Right (ContentType TypeText)
410--
411--   Recursive contents.
412--
413--     >>> stringC "[ 'foo | 'bar ]"
414--     Right (ContentList [ContentCode "foo", ContentCode "bar"])
415--
416--     >>> stringC "{ 'foo | 'bar }"
417--     Right (ContentSet [ContentCode "foo", ContentCode "bar"])
418--
419--     >>> stringC "{- /x 'foo /y 'bar -}"
420--     Right (ContentTie [("x", ContentCode "foo"), ("y", ContentCode "bar")])
421--
422--     >>> stringC "{= /x /y [ 'foo | 'bar ][ 'baz | 'qux ] =}"
423--     Right (ContentRel (Rel { relHead = ..., relBody = ... }))
424--
425stringC :: String -> B.Ab Content
426stringC = D.stringContent
